Extra xkb config to extend base US layout with our umlauts. Idea from
https://www.karl.berlin/umlauts.html that itself got infomration from a
[3-part blog post](https://who-t.blogspot.com/2020/08/user-specific-xkb-configuration-part-3.html)

- [another blog post](https://codeaffen.org/2023/09/16/custom-keyboard-layouts-with-xkb/)
  describinig creation of custom layouts
  - note it [mentions](https://codeaffen.org/2023/09/16/custom-keyboard-layouts-with-xkb/#adding-an-option)
    having to create a `~/.config/xkb/rules/evdev` that refrences our new file.
    unconfirmed whether it's really needed or not
  - also note it [mentions](https://codeaffen.org/2023/09/16/custom-keyboard-layouts-with-xkb/#localectl)
    `localectl` won't pick up custom config under ~/.confg, and links to a relevant
    systemd issue!!

Note this comment on keyd umlauts issue/discussion also suggests going
xkb route: https://github.com/rvaiya/keyd/issues/470#issuecomment-1843065356

# some commands:

- get current keyboard variant settings: `localectl status`
- list all avail layouts: `localectl list-x11-keymap-layouts`
- list avail keybaord variants: `localectl list-x11-keymap-variants`
- list all variants for given layout: `localectl list-x11-keymap-variants us`
- list available toggle options: `localectl list-x11-keymap-options`
- see current active keyboard setting: `setxkbmap -print -verbose 10`

# troubleshooting

If custom layout is not found/loaded, consider:
- https://askubuntu.com/questions/1537309/my-xkb-custom-keyboard-layout-is-no-longer-working-after-restart
- if using sway, we possibly have to define used layout in its config file per [this arch comment](https://bbs.archlinux.org/viewtopic.php?pid=2213207#p2213207)
- per [this custom layout installation project readme](https://codeberg.org/mateowoetam/halmaklinuxsupport/src/branch/master/halmak-mutable)
  X11 may not be supported when config is installed under `~/.config`
  - think with x11 we need to [define our config](https://codeaffen.org/2022/02/07/custom-keyboard-layout/)
    directly in `/usr/share/X11/xkb/symbols/` dir

# see also:

- [libxkbcommon docs](https://xkbcommon.org/doc/current/user-configuration.html) on user conf

